Scope Boundaries

The scope boundaries define the limits of CookSnap â€“ Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images by clearly 
specifying what the system will and will not do. This helps avoid ambiguity and ensures that the project remains focused on its intended objectives.

Included Within Scope

Uploading images of available groceries by users

Automatic detection of ingredients using image recognition

Recommendation of suitable recipes based on detected ingredients

Display of recipe details including ingredients and preparation steps

Basic filtering of recipes (e.g., vegetarian / non-vegetarian)

User authentication and access control

Basic usage statistics and system monitoring

Excluded from Scope

Online grocery purchasing, payment processing, or delivery services

Personalized dietary, nutritional, or medical advice

Live cooking classes or video-based tutorials

Advanced meal planning and scheduling features

Integration with smart kitchen appliances or IoT devices

Advanced analytics, calorie tracking, or nutrition forecasting

Integration with third-party e-commerce or food delivery platforms

System Boundaries

The CookSnap system operates as a standalone software application focused solely on identifying groceries from images and recommending appropriate recipes.
It functions as a decision-support tool for meal planning and does not replace professional nutritional advice or provide health-related recommendations.
